Assume `data.txt` contains two lines: `hello` and `world`. What does this program print to **stdout**?

```cpp
#include <fstream>
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
int main() {
    std::ifstream f("data.txt");
    int count = 0;
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(f, line)) ++count;
    std::cout << count << "\n";
}
```
